---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Terms of Service | Margin Theory"
  description="Terms governing use of margintheory.co and Margin Theory engagements."
>
  <section>
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 pt-24 pb-12 md:pt-32">
      <div class="text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-margin-blue font-semibold mb-6">Legal</div>
      <h1 class="text-5xl md:text-6xl font-bold tracking-tight leading-[1.05] mb-6">
        Terms of Service
      </h1>
      <p class="text-sm text-white/50">Last updated: April 17, 2026</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 pb-20">
      <div class="space-y-8 text-base md:text-lg text-white/80 leading-relaxed">
        <p>
          These Terms of Service ("Terms") govern your use of margintheory.co and any engagement with Margin Theory.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-white pt-6">About Margin Theory</h2>
        <p>
          Margin Theory is a fractional CFO practice operated by Jake Erickson. We provide monthly financial review, forecasting, cash flow planning, and related advisory services to founder-led businesses from Austin, Texas.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-white pt-6">Engagement Agreement Governs</h2>
        <p>
          Client services are governed by a separate written engagement agreement between Margin Theory and the client. The engagement agreement controls all aspects of the services, fees, term, termination, confidentiality, and scope of work. Nothing on margintheory.co is an offer to provide services absent a signed engagement agreement.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-white pt-6">Website Use</h2>
        <p>margintheory.co is an informational website. By using it you agree:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
          <li>Not to use the site for unlawful purposes</li>
          <li>Not to attempt to interfere with the site's operation</li>
          <li>Not to scrape or republish content without written permission</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-white pt-6">Not Legal, Tax, Accounting, or Investment Advice</h2>
        <p>
          Content on margintheory.co is for general information only. It is not legal advice, tax advice, accounting advice, or investment advice. Before acting on any information you should consult a qualified professional familiar with your specific situation.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-white pt-6">QuickBooks Online Integration</h2>
        <p>
          Margin Theory uses QuickBooks Online APIs solely to deliver services to engaged clients. Clients who authorize Margin Theory as a user of their QBO company may revoke that access at any time through QuickBooks. The internal tool used to call QBO ("Margin Theory CFO Prep") is not sold, licensed, or distributed to third parties.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-white pt-6">Intellectual Property</h2>
        <p>
          Content on margintheory.co, including written materials, frameworks, and branding, is owned by Margin Theory. Clients receive a limited license to use deliverables (workbooks, plans, dashboards) produced under their engagement for their own business purposes.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-white pt-6">No Warranty</h2>
        <p>
          margintheory.co and any information on it is provided "as is" without warranty of any kind, express or implied.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-white pt-6">Limitation of Liability</h2>
        <p>
          To the fullest extent permitted by law, Margin Theory is not liable for indirect, incidental, special, or consequential damages arising from use of margintheory.co or reliance on its content. For services rendered under an engagement agreement, liability is governed exclusively by that agreement.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-white pt-6">Governing Law</h2>
        <p>
          These Terms are governed by the laws of the State of Texas without regard to conflict of laws principles. Any dispute arising from these Terms shall be resolved in the state or federal courts located in Travis County, Texas.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-white pt-6">Changes</h2>
        <p>
          We may update these Terms from time to time. The "last updated" date at the top reflects the current version.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-white pt-6">Contact</h2>
        <p>
          Margin Theory<br>
          Attn: Jake Erickson<br>
          <a href="mailto:jake@margintheory.co" class="text-margin-blue hover:underline">jake@margintheory.co</a><br>
          Austin, Texas
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
